ate for the norm of the inverse of a\nGaussian matrix, prove such an estimate also in the case of a sparse Gaussian\nmatrix, present some novel advanced pre-processing techniques for fast and\nsuperfast computation of LRA, and extend our results to dramatic acceleration\nof the Fast Multipole Method (FMM) and the Conjugate Gradient algorithms.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 22 Oct 2017 14:11:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 1 Nov 2017 19:00:42 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 4 Nov 2017 03:26:56 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 10 Jan 2018 13:53:37 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Fri, 12 Jan 2018 02:22:44 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Tue, 13 Mar 2018 11:51:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-08"}
